  "unmapped_findings": [
    "The as-received material was in an electroslag remelted (ESR) condition before homogenization.",
    "True-stress-strain curves under compression exhibit mechanical stability over 200–500 °C and a significant stress drop from 500 to 600 °C; appreciable flow softening after true strain of 0.3 at 500–600 °C is attributed to strain-induced transformations. Quantitative flow stress values were not provided in the text (tabular values in the supplied Fig. 1d appear to be pipeline artifacts).",
    "Chemical composition of constituent phases after deformation at 500 °C measured by SEM-EDS: ferrite contains 10.3 ± 0.1 wt.% Mn and 6.0 ± 0.1 wt.% Al; austenite contains 12.8 ± 0.1 wt.% Mn and 4.7 ± 0.1 wt.% Al.",
    "The stacking fault energy of the steel is reported as 80–110 mJ/m2, which theoretically suppresses austenite-to-martensite transformation.",
    "Active slip systems in ferrite during warm deformation at 500 °C were identified as {110}<111> and {112}<111>, promoting slip-band intersection and formation of high-dislocation-density walls (HDDWs)."
  ]
}